    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "In the following script I use a canvas size of 10 x 10 cm and 100 dots per cm. It should create an image of 1000 x 1000 pixels. The information says so but I got an image of 1001 x 1001 pixels (and ffmpeg fails to create a movie from image with even pixels).\r\n\r\nError message:\r\n![imagen](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17908951/128806179-e1b13c4f-89d1-423f-b0c7-71d47770bf65.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nFull Script:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\r\n\r\ncat << 'EOF' > pre.sh\r\ngmt begin\r\n    gmt math -T0/3/1 T SIND -o0,1,0 = > line.txt  \r\n    gmt events line.txt -R-40/400/-2/2 -JX8c/8c -Ar200i > line_points.txt\r\ngmt end\r\nEOF\r\n\r\ncat << 'EOF' > main.sh\r\ngmt begin\r\n    gmt events -R-40/400/-2/2 -JX8c/8c -Baf -B+t\"Snake line\" line_points.txt -Ar -T${MOVIE_COL0} -Es -W2p,red -Yc -Xc\r\ngmt end\r\nEOF\r\n\r\ngmt movie \"main.sh\" -Sb\"pre.sh\" -N\"Lines3\" -T\"line.txt\" -C10cx10cx100 -Vi -Ml,png -Fmp4 -Zs\r\n\r\nrm  line*.txt\r\n```",
