            "body": "Another question, in the previous script I try to use this\r\n```\r\n\r\ngmt begin\r\n    gmt math -T0/300/1 T SIND -o0,1,0 = > line.txt\r\n    gmt basemap -R-40/400/-2/2 -JX10c/10c -B+n -Yc -Xc\r\n    gmt events line.txt                -Ar100c > line_points.txt  # Do NOT work\r\ngmt end\r\n```\r\n\r\n but I got the error:\r\n\r\n`events [ERROR]: Must specify -R option`\r\n\r\nWhen I use this it worked:\r\n`    gmt events line.txt -R-40/400/-2/2 -Ar100c > line_points.txt  # Work`\r\n\r\n\r\ngmt event should not be able to read -R from the line above? \r\n\r\nWhen I use gmt events without -Ardpu (just -Ar -T) I do not have this problem.",
